prediction.overall_explanation: The contract only allows anyone to increment an internal, private counter (sellerBalance). There is no ether handling, no external interactions, and no logic that depends on the correctness of sellerBalance for authorization or value transfers. Overflow of sellerBalance or unrestricted write access therefore cannot be leveraged for a meaningful attack. No real, exploitable vulnerability was identified.
